  <source>University Hospital, Clermont-Ferrand</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A previous study has shown that tropisetron inhibits the analgesic effect of paracetamol in
      healthy volunteers. This study aims at confirming this pharmacodynamic interaction in
      patients with post-surgery pain.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The study is a comparison of the analgesic action of paracetamol versus tropisetron +
      paracetamol in 30 patients who had surgery of the ear. The evaluation criteria will be the
      score on the visual analogue scale for pain evaluation.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
